7:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1241.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Any suggestion</span><hr size=1> Hello to you all,<br>
First of all, I'm sorry for my poor english but I'm french, if it causes any trouble for someone to read bad english, OK, I'll write in french <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I play on Karana server and I plan to change to FV server (I've been playing RPG since 17 years now and I'm kinda upset with people who looks at me as if I were crazy when I RP, poor them). My goals on FV server are multiple :<br>
- I want to see the world, as my main is only 22 on Karana, I didn't see lotsa things,<br>
- I want to see the high levels, not in irder to become uber or so, just feel the power flowing through my keyboard <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , same reason as precedent point, and I've been playing EQ since 2 years, but in a cybercafe, so my characters didn't went up very fast, and I preferes guild event and knowing people more than leveling, so...<br>
- I want to be self sufficient, not that I want to be one of those hard soloers, but, to my mind, a self sufficient guys is a pretty welcome new for a group as he can do all that is needed. In fact, I just plan on soloing at the beginning of each level just to raise defense skill <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ,<br>
- I want spells,<br>
- I want to be needed. Not from an egoistic point of view, but more in the sens of people saying, damn, a &quot;put class here&quot; ! Since when didn't I see one of these guys ?<br>
- The evil, neutral or good way are unimportant to me, I can rp anything and I've already been rped anything since 17 years of RPG. Don't worry, has I stated before, I come BECAUSE OF roleplay.<br>
- More than all, I come to make friends <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
- Is there a lot of +0 GMT players/guilds ? I'd prefer joining such a guild in order to be able to see my guildmates without having to go to bed at 11:00 AM because some guild event started at 8:00 PM EST.<br>
<br>
So I was hesitating between :<br>
- druid, I'm sure I'd enjoy the class, not because it's powerfull but because it's a jack of all trades,<br>
- shaman, I really enjoy this class, but I already have 2 shaman and starting again is a pain in the a$$ (though my highest shaman is only 15, so this would be a short term feeling I think),<br>
- necro,<br>
- wizard.<br>
Speaking about the race, I really don't mind.<br>
May I, please, require your ideas and/or suggestions please ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukratekitris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krate Kitris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 12:58:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1241.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Any suggestion</span><hr size=1> Be a Bard Frenchie.  And then you can see the world as you run super fast through it so the mobs don't bite your head off. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulexxiclockwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lexxi Clockwork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 1:16:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1241.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Any suggestion</span><hr size=1>      Gnome wizard or warrior. Warrior because they seem to be very far between and us clerics do not want to get hit. Wizard because of the fast put down power, especially with the shortage of warriors.<br>
     Also we are having a guild caravan on Friday Feb. 2nd at 8pm CST (2am GMT) we will travel from Ak'Anon to Kelethin where we will have a picnic and sell our wares.<br>
<br>
Lexxi Ledenyetz<br>
25th Prayer<br>
Cleric of Brell<br>
Ak'Anon<br>
Officer and Heiress - Ledenyetz Troupe<br>
<br>
PS. we have members form GMT -1:00 to GMT -8:00 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulexxiclockwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lexxi Clockwork</A> at: 1/31/02 1:35:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utrinnityfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trinnity FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 2:15:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1241.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Any suggestion</span><hr size=1> For solo, necro or druid.<br>
<br>
If you really want to travel all the lands, then druid, hands down.  The SOW and teleports of this class are not to be overlooked.  On Xegony, I practically solo'd to 57.  However, be sure to group when you can because it is much more enjoyable then soloing (IMHO).<br>
<br>
Alternatively, Wizards are good travellers as well but a bit more group dependant.<br>
<br>
From what you've outlined, you would do well with a druid (although there ARE a lot of the tree hugging spuds on FV).<br>
<br>
Good luck and you did well with the language...I think everyone understood you.<br>
<br>
 <p>Trinnity X'Vex <BR>
Shadowknight <BR>
Indigo Void <BR>
Firiona Vie <BR><BR>
"For Hate's sake, I spit at thee..."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 2:33:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1241.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Any suggestion</span><hr size=1> As second language English goes, that was pretty good.  No worries.  For all but your desire to be wanted in groups, I'd suggest druid, as others have.  That isn't to say druids are not welcome in my groups, but I can't recall often sitting around and thinking &quot;This group would really be rocking if we only had another druid!&quot;  Truth is, the ability of a class to solo and the usefulness of that class in a group are almost directly opposite to one another.  Any class can be effective in a group, but the ones that can really change the entire nature of a group just aren't built to solo.<br>
<br>
All of that being said, I'd suggest wizard.  You can teleport at least, and get to different parts of the world.  You have spells, as you were seeking, and can solo (I know of wizards who have soloed quite high) but you are still far better in a group.  And real wizard nuking is far too lacking in most places I've seen.  Nuking druids, sure.  A reasonable amount of mages, etc., and even enough clerics you sometimes see clerics turning DD when there are two or three in a group, but no one really touches wizards when it comes to this.  More wizards would be most welcome.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps.<br>
<br>
Valquiss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giver of da juice (tm)</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 2:52:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1241.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Any suggestion</span><hr size=1> Ya, druid is certainly a self sufficient class and great for exploring with the teleport abilities.<br>
<br>
The bard is also a highly under rated class. Its also one of the classes that always seem to be lacking at the high end game. Its one of the few classes in EQ where its truly the players finesse and skill that make the class come alive. <p>Kzan Verto<BR>
Giver of "da juice" (tm)
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=viren>Viren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 2:56:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1241.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Any suggestion</span><hr size=1> You could always play a troll or ogre, that way when you don't feel like struggling with the language, you can just roleplay it away. =)<br>
<br>
-=Viren=- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uraycoom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raycoom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 2:58:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1241.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Any suggestion</span><hr size=1> I think there is a exception to the rule here. And that would be a Bard.<br>
<br>
To solo with a bard takes skill, but under most outdoor conditions theres NO class that can do it better.... if you have the skill to do it that is, because its hard... its hard to do and its hard on your hands heh. That said, this class is also GREAT in groups, I'd personally put them at the bottom of the top 5 group classes in the game.<br>
<br>
If I didn't hate their RP angle so much I'd certainly be playing one on FV still.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 340<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 4:02:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1241.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well, you don't ..</span><hr size=1> .. want to be a warrior.  If there's a less self-sufficient class out there, I don't know it.  If you want good group and good solo, I'd say shaman.  Druid does well, too.  Bard is great, but twisting songs is not for most -- and especially not for those without some form of gamepad.<br>
<br>
If you want to see everything, play a rogue.  No class scouts better than a rogue.  They don't solo very well, though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=damah>Damah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 4:38:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1241.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well, you don't ..</span><hr size=1> As has been said, shaman can solo and group well.  He can also explore with relative ease.  A shaman can summon his own food and water.  He can summon a 100% reduction container for when you become encumbered.  Shaman also have speed, levitation, size changing and I believe invis spells for travel. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyrdup.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyrd Up</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 170<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 4:59:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1241.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmm</span><hr size=1> enchanter too.<br>
<br>
They are highly wanted/needed in groups.<br>
You can also solo.<br>
You always get the best prices from vendors (hey it's a nice little bonus) because of your awesome charisma!<br>
Illusions rock.<br>
<br>
negatives.. at the very high end game (doubt you'll be worry about it), they are still wanted for clarity and haste... but can do little else in major raids. But single groups will always be fun.<br>
